        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 2:08AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 208 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marion, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Home Corner, Landess, Lancaster, Plum Tree, Hanfield, Warren,
Majenica, Banquo, Mount Etna, Marion, Van Buren, Lake Wood, Pleasant
Plain, Andrews, and Gas City.

This includes Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 265 and
282.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
